Touch a willing creature and grant it the following for 1 minute:
It can make 1 additional attack;
It can Dash as a Bonus action;
It gains +2 AC and +2 to Dexterity saving throws;
If it ends its turn without having dealt damage to a hostile creature since the end of its prior turn, it takes 1d{{rite die:size}} necrotic damage.
Once the effect ends the creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC {{rite die:dc}}) or suffer one exhaustion level.

Make a Vital Sacrifice to enter your Beast Form of CR 1 or lower without a flying or swimming speed. You retain your current and maximum hit points. While in this form, gain:
{{beast form tmp hp}} temporary hit points;
The ability to regain +{{constitution:modifier}} hit points each turn as long as you have more than 1 and less than half your hit points;
Advantage on attack rolls against creatures marked by Crimson Brand;
Resistance to non-magical, non-silvered bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage; your natural weapons count as magical when considering resistances and use d{{rite die:size}}s for damage unless their natural damage is higher. If you are holding a Crimson Offering weapon upon transformation, its effects transfer to one of your Form's weapons
You remain in this form for 1 hr. or until you are incapacitated or revert with a bonus action. You can make another Vital Sacrifice to remain at the end of the hour.

